C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%2C%20sustainability%20is%20hinged%20on%20a%2095%20percent%20dependence%20on%20local%20produce.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20believe%20in%20everything%20coming%20from%20within%2040%20sq%20km%20of%20the%20village.%20Only%20then%20will%20the%20communities%20see%20a%20direct%20benefit.%20Only%20then%20will%20they%20see%20tourism%20from%20a%20very%20different%20angle%2C%E2%80%9D%20Amit%20underscores.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20look%20at%20the%20Sankhala%20lineage%20suggests%20that%20nature%20has%20always%20held%20a%20relatively%20reverential%20spot.%20And%20this%20love%20traces%20back%20to%20Kailash%20Sankhala.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EEarly%20childhood%20and%20expeditions%20in%20the%20jungle%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%2C%20elephants%20and%20squirrels%20were%20Amit%E2%80%99s%20best%20friends.%20The%20destinations%20of%20choice%20for%20childhood%20vacations%20were%20national%20parks%20and%20sanctuaries%2C%20while%20his%20grandfather%20Kailash%20undertook%20research%20projects%20in%20and%20of%20the%20wild.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20shares%20with%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%2C%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99d%20go%20with%20him%20%5BKailash%5D%20for%20weeks%20to%20Ranthambore%20%5BNational%20Park%20in%20Rajasthan%5D%2C%E2%80%9D%20Amit%20has%20fond%20memories.%20To%20him%2C%20Kailash%20was%20the%20reason%20for%20his%20camaraderie%20with%20nature%3B%20India%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20remembers%20Kailash%20as%20being%20synonymous%20with%20Project%20Tiger.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fjamtara-wilderness-camp-4-1753447168.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kailash%20Sankhala%20was%20chosen%20by%20Shrimati%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20to%20head%20Project%20Tiger%20initiative%20in%